(762, 1, '2014-01-11 13:04:44', '2014-01-11 18:04:44', 'Marc Andreesen said “Markets that don’t exist don’t care how smart you are.” Whether you’re a startup founder trying to disrupt an industry, or an intrapreneur trying to provoke change from within, your biggest risk is building something nobody wants. The Lean Startup movement has transformed the way we grow new companies, and with good reason: rather than making big, reckless bets, it focuses on a constant cycle of learning.\r\n\r\nAt the core of the cycle is analytics. By measuring and analyzing as you grow, you can validate whether a problem is real, find the right customers, and decide what to build, how to monetize it, and how to spread the word. The best-selling <i>Lean Analytics</i> shows you how to put data to work, whether you’re a founder of a new startup or an intrapreneur trying to create change from within. In this session, we’ll look at the five stages of innovation, and how to apply these lessons to new companies, existing organizations, and even governments.', 'Lean Analytics: Using Data to Build A Better Business Faster', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'lean-analytics-using-data-build-better-business-faster', '', '', '2014-02-24 09:38:22', '2014-02-24 14:38:22', '', 0, 'http://waq2014.lvh.me/?post_type=session&#038;p=762', 0, 'session', '', 0),
