(1322, 7, '2014-03-03 09:57:58', '2014-03-03 14:57:58', 'The push for Open Data has reach a milestone. Governments everywhere - abroad, in Canada and Quebec - are launching open data portals. There is now more data is available for developers, non-profits, companies and individuals to play with than ever before.\r\n\r\nSo now what?\r\n\r\nThe conversation about Open Data is entering a new phase. The focus will be less about if to do open data than about what it will mean. New opportunities will emerge for for-profit and non-profit players to offer new services. But there will also be challenges as data itself becomes more political and contested. Least talked about is how open data will change how governments organize their IT with implications for web developers and IT vendors more generally.\r\n\r\nWhether an entrepreneur, web developer or a engaged citizen - David’s talk will share the latest thinking around open data and push your thinking about both the emerging challenges and opportunity.', 'Open Data and Developers, Where Next?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '764-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-03 09:57:58', '2014-03-03 14:57:58', '', 764, 'http://waq2014.lvh.me/2014/03/03/764-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(1323, 7, '2014-03-03 12:42:30', '2014-03-03 17:42:30', 'In Canada, 69% of consumers expect to be able to use a credit card where they shop. But for many of the local businesses, accepting credit cards is too complicated and expensive. More than two thirds of small businesses in Canada don’t accept credit cards for this reason, leaving hundreds and thousands of small businesses in Canada unable to meet their customers’ expectations and without this key tool. Square started to solve this very real problem because every seller should have the tools to make selling simple. With the right tools made affordable and accessible, every seller – individual or small business – never has to miss an opportunity to participate in commerce.', 'Making Commerce Easy ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '760-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-03-03 12:42:30', '2014-03-03 17:42:30', '', 760, 'http://waq2014.lvh.me/2014/03/03/760-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
